The correct answer is:
They should be able to design and implement systems that involve the integration of software and hardware devices.
→ Computer engineers,
They should be able to analyze information requirements and business processes and be able specify and design systems that are aligned with organizational goals.
→ Information systems specialists,
They should be able to work effectively at planning, implementation, configuration, and maintenance of an organization’s computing infrastructure.
→ Information technology professionals,
They should be able to properly perform and manage activities at every stage of the life cycle of large-scale software systems.
→ Software engineers,
They should be prepared to work in a broad range of positions involving tasks from theoretical work to software development.
→ Computer scientists
